==English==

===Etymology===
From the Greek prefix '''[[tele-]]''' (transmission over a distance), plus Japanese [[津波]] / [[津浪]] ([[つなみ]], tsunami), "harbour wave".

===Pronunciation===
*telə-tso͞o-nä'mi, /tɛlə-tsuˈnɑːmi/, /<tt>tEl&-tsu-nA:mi</tt>/
*telə-so͞o-nä'mi, /tɛlə-suˈnɑːmi/, /<tt>tEl&-su-nA:mi</tt>/

===Noun===
'''teletsunami''' (''Plural:'' '''teletsunamis''' ''or'' '''teletsunami''')

# A '''teletsunami''' is a [[tsunami]] that travels more than 1000 km from its source before impacting upon an area.

